Whether providing product information, performing a price check, or making a sale, being able to move throughout the location is critical. As more customers demand high speed retail, mobile points of sale are becoming absolute necessities.

data.name: RetailMCRSubDescB
data.value: Employees are no longer stuck at a cash wrap with mobile points of sale. Able to handle traditional POS functions on the go, store employees can interact with customers and perform other job duties on the floor in between sales.

data.name: RetailMCRSubDescC
data.value: For line busting, employees can become points of sale from any location when cashier backup is needed. Customers picking up just a few items can be quickly out of the store. And, since points of sale have moved beyond the traditional cash wrap, it is easy to scale the points of sale with extra employees and devices for peak times or seasons.

data.name: RetailMCRSubDescD
data.value: By eliminating or reducing stationary points of sale, retailers reclaim floor space for additional merchandise, expanded cross merchandising, interactive experiences, lounge areas to encourage lingering in stores—the possibilities are endless.

data.name: RetailMCRTag
data.value: Enable Mobile Cash Registers now with the apps and policies to increase efficiency, allow for more floor space and help with line busting.

data.name: RetailMISESubDescA
data.value: With self-service kiosks, customers are engaged with your brand and an in-store experience, even if an employee isn’t available. Customers enjoy the efficiency of shopping, looking for and comparing products, checking inventory and purchasing.

data.name: RetailMISESubDescB
data.value: Store customers can browse style guides, brochures, purchase history and size preferences. Just in time coupons and promotions can help push customers to purchase.

data.name: RetailMISESubDescC
data.value: Customers experience a curated, branded experience whenever they enter a store with digital signage. Using custom apps to create signage to differentiate your brand that can be changed easily when styles, promotions and seasons change.

data.name: RetailMISESubDescD
data.value: Customers only have access to the app you’ve selected or designed with single app mode, so devices are only used for their intended purpose—giving you complete control over their experience and making sure devices settings aren’t changed.

data.name: RetailMISETag
data.value: Enhance Customer In Store Experiences with mobility now with the apps and policies to encourage self-service and interaction with your brand, without sacrificing security.

data.name: RetailSMSubDescA
data.value: Retail managers are critical to the success of their locations. With inventory reporting, revenue forecasts, sales reports, employee schedules, payroll and more, managers are always multitasking. To supervise employees, monitor the store and assist customers, it’s important for managers to maximize time on the floor rather than behind a desk.

data.name: RetailSMSubDescB
data.value: Managers can get out of the back room and work on reports, employee schedules and payroll from anywhere in the store. With access to workflows, transactions, mobile operations systems access, inventory management, multimedia, customer information and business intelligence, managers have the right information in real time to help make impactful, strategic decisions.

data.name: RetailSMSubDescC
data.value: Managers can effectively communicate and collaborate with employees, other managers and headquarters with mobile email, phone calls and messaging, and file sharing.

data.name: RetailSMTag
data.value: Empower Store Managers now with the apps and policies to manage the day-to-day operations, manage employees and communicate for effective collaboration.

data.name: RuntimeProvisioningInfo
data.value:
Windows 10 allows devices to be easily provisioned in bulk using a pre-configured package. You can use the Windows Imaging and Configuration Designer tool to create a single staging package and use this package to stage all your devices.
To automatically map the devices to the end users, register devices per user or using a bulk import before creating the provisioning package.
In order to create the provisioning package please follow the steps below:
1. Copy the displayed configurations into the Workplace section of the Windows Imaging and Configuration Designer. 2. Use the UPN of the staging user that has been generated for you or any staging user that has been created in the system. 3. Save and export the provisioning package to a removable drive. 4. Add the package to the device by clicking on it or adding it using the Accounts/Work Access page.
The device will enroll into AirWatch and be assigned to the registered user.
